<T>__{cut to:}
<L>__{interior phyllis bernard's office day}
<A>__{it is a real mess, legal files and law books scattered everywhere. in the midst of all this chaos sits phyllis bernard, as we said before, she is about thirty, very pretty in spite of her glasses.}
<B>__{on phyllis}
<A>__{she looks up as ted enters. it is clear from their attitude that they have known one another for a long time and are very relaxed together.}
<C>__{phyllis}
<D>__{hello, kramer.}
<B>__{on ted}
<A>__{he drops into a chair and shoves a stack of papers across the desk to her.}
<C>__{ted}
<D>__{hiya, phyllis. these are the revlon contracts. i thought you ought to check them out.}
<C>__{phyllis}
<D>__{sure.}
<A>__{she takes the papers and starts to rifle through them, stopping every so often and making a note in the margin. as she does, we notice that the second and third buttons of her blouse have come undone and that she is not wearing a bra.}
<B>__{closer on ted}
<A>__{as he realizes this.}
<B>__{on phyllis}
<A>__{she glances up to ask ted a question about some point or other, notices the direction of his gaze and, unself consciously buttons up her blouse. she goes back to her papers as ted continues to watch her.}
<B>__{on phyllis}
<A>__{not looking up from her papers.}
<C>__{phyllis}
<D>__{yes.}
<C>__{ted}
<P>__{(baffled)}
<D>__{yes, what?}
<C>__{phyllis}
<P>__{(looks up, serious)}
<D>__{yes, i will have dinner with you.}
